gg, Baron Rees-Mogg, (14 July 192829 December 2012) was an English journalist and public servant. He served as editor of "The Times" (1967–81), chairman of the Arts Council of Great Britain, and vice-chairman of the BBC.', 'Dudley Carew | Dudley Charles Carew (born 1903; died on 22 March 1981 at Cuckfield, Sussex aged 77) was an English journalist, writer, poet and film critic. He was a special correspondent of "The Times" in the 1920s and 1930s, and reported on cricket matches for the paper. From 1945 until his retirement in 1963 he was the paper\'s film critic. Almost all his articles for "The Times" were written anonymously, as was the paper\'s policy until William Rees-Mogg became its editor in 1967.', 'Geoffrey Crawley | Geoffrey Crawley (10 December 1926 – 29 October 2010) was a photographic expert and journalist, and was the editor in chief of "British Journal of Photography" for two decades. He was noted for exposing the photographs of the Cottingley Fairies taken in the early 20th century as a hoax.'], 'question': "Thomas Richard Morris' daughter married an English journalist who served as the editor of what?", 'reasoning': 'The question asks about Thomas Richard Morris\' daughter marrying an English journalist. According to the context, Thomas Richard Morris\' daughter Gillian Shakespeare married William Rees-Mogg, an English journalist. To answer this question, we need to look at the information provided in the context about William Rees-Mogg\'s career.\n\nWilliam Rees-Mogg served as the editor of "The Times" from 1967 to 1981.', 'answer': '"The Times"'}) (input_keys=None), Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['Martha Bulloch Roosevelt | Martha Bulloch "Mittie" Roosevelt (born Martha Stewart Bulloch; July 8, 1835 – February 14, 1884) was an American socialite. She was also the mother of US President Theodore Roosevelt and the paternal grandmother of Eleanor Roosevelt. She was a great-granddaughter of Archibald Bulloch, grandniece of William Bellinger B